President Donald J. Trump has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to the Kingdom of Belgium and the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg for the World War II Battle of the Bulge 75th Anniversary Commemoration Events on December 16, 2019. The delegation will be led by Secretary of Defense Dr. Mark T. Esper and includes United States Ambassador to the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg, J. Randolph Evans, United States Ambassador to the Kingdom of Belgium, Ronald J. Gidwitz, Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, General Mark A. Milley, United States Permanent Representative to NATO, Kay Bailey Hutchison, and Chairman of the American Battle Monuments Commission, David J. Urban.